    {
        "content": "<p>The point is that this in Lean is a <em>definition</em> rather than a theorem: we don't say \"this set is a basis\", but we define it as a basis (moreover a basis is something slightly more complicated than a set)</p>",
        "id": 446255649,
        "sender_full_name": "Riccardo Brasca",
        "timestamp": 1719051414
